<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 4:53PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northwestern
Richland, southwestern Huron, southeastern Seneca and northern
Crawford Counties through 530 PM EDT...
At 453 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Bloomville to near Chatfield to 7 miles
southeast of Sycamore. Movement was southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mansfield, Bucyrus, Shelby, Willard, Ontario, Crestline, Plymouth,
New Washington, Bloomville, Chatfield, Attica, Benton, North
Fairfield, Republic, Tiro and Sulpher Springs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
